1
00:00:09,100 --> 00:00:10,100
<i> They're siblings.</i>

2
00:00:10,233 --> 00:00:11,167
<i> What did you say?</i>

3
00:00:11,300 --> 00:00:13,200
<i> Edward and Paolo are brothers.</i>

4
00:00:13,333 --> 00:00:17,067
<i>I thought you said Jasmine and
your child were the siblings.</i>

5
00:00:17,200 --> 00:00:19,467
<i>What? How would that
even happen?</i>

6
00:00:19,600 --> 00:00:21,800
<i>Is this what you looked like
as a baby?</i>

7
00:00:21,933 --> 00:00:23,667
<i>He actually looks more like
your older brother.</i>

8
00:00:23,800 --> 00:00:26,367
<i>Your niece is beautiful
and healthy, Paolo.</i>

9
00:00:26,500 --> 00:00:28,233
<i> Don't you ever forget that.</i>

10
00:00:28,367 --> 00:00:29,300
<i> She's Edward's child.</i>

11
00:00:29,433 --> 00:00:30,900
<i>Why do you look like
you're about to cry?</i>

12
00:00:31,033 --> 00:00:33,167
<i>Your husband just feels guilty.</i>

13
00:00:33,300 --> 00:00:36,933
<i>Because he and Edward still
aren't okay.</i>

14
00:00:37,100 --> 00:00:40,367
<i>With Edward's team, we can build
something big in Cebu.</i>

15
00:00:40,500 --> 00:00:41,667
<i> When do you plan to relocate?</i>

16
00:00:41,800 --> 00:00:44,300
<i>Why am I only hearing
about this now?</i>

17
00:00:46,300 --> 00:00:47,833
Hon.

18
00:00:47,967 --> 00:00:50,100
I'm sorry I didn't tell you
sooner.

19
00:00:51,633 --> 00:00:53,900
I'm doing this for our future.

20
00:00:54,033 --> 00:00:56,567
You know Cebu is one of the
fastest-growing IT hubs

21
00:00:56,700 --> 00:00:57,567
in the country right now.

22
00:00:57,700 --> 00:00:59,667
We have a bigger chance
of succeeding there.

23
00:00:59,800 --> 00:01:01,067
But, Edward,

24
00:01:01,200 --> 00:01:03,467
we'll be far from your family.

25
00:01:03,600 --> 00:01:06,167
From Mom Regina and Daddy Greg.

26
00:01:06,300 --> 00:01:08,833
Ashley will be far from the
Torrecampo family as well.

27
00:01:09,000 --> 00:01:10,100
You know...

28
00:01:10,233 --> 00:01:11,700
Hon, we'll come back.

29
00:01:11,833 --> 00:01:13,767
- What?
- For holidays, birthdays.

30
00:01:13,900 --> 00:01:15,667
Of course, we'll be there.

31
00:01:15,800 --> 00:01:16,767
We'll show up.

32
00:01:18,733 --> 00:01:21,400
Hon, have you seen
the projections?

33
00:01:21,533 --> 00:01:23,400
The numbers?

34
00:01:23,533 --> 00:01:25,700
We can really make it big
in Cebu.

35
00:01:25,833 --> 00:01:28,967
Those dreams we've been talking
about can finally come true,

36
00:01:29,100 --> 00:01:31,267
our life will get better,
for us.

37
00:01:31,500 --> 00:01:32,767
Isn't that what you've always
wanted?

38
00:01:34,467 --> 00:01:36,033
And dad...

39
00:01:36,167 --> 00:01:38,800
I'll finally prove to him
I'm not a failure.

40
00:01:38,933 --> 00:01:40,967
He'll look at me differently,
Hon.

41
00:01:43,133 --> 00:01:44,333
And our child?

42
00:01:44,467 --> 00:01:46,567
Yes, of course.

43
00:01:48,433 --> 00:01:50,867
Just make sure, Edward,

44
00:01:51,000 --> 00:01:52,600
that this move to Cebu...

45
00:01:53,633 --> 00:01:54,967
doesn't end in failure.

46
00:01:56,300 --> 00:01:57,767
Especially now...

47
00:01:57,900 --> 00:01:59,433
that Ashley's here.

48
00:02:01,033 --> 00:02:04,833
Don't you ever fail us.

49
00:02:06,567 --> 00:02:08,233
That will never happen.

50
00:03:04,200 --> 00:03:06,667
We just came from the hospital,
Mom.

51
00:03:06,800 --> 00:03:10,933
The doctor said Jasmine's
doing better.

52
00:03:11,067 --> 00:03:12,967
So I brought her straight here.

53
00:03:14,500 --> 00:03:16,667
Thank God, Marj.

54
00:03:18,067 --> 00:03:20,500
But why isn't Paolo with you?

55
00:03:20,667 --> 00:03:23,933
He's been watching over Jasmine
nonstop for days.

56
00:03:24,067 --> 00:03:26,067
He just needs some rest.

57
00:03:26,200 --> 00:03:28,600
We're okay again.

58
00:03:28,733 --> 00:03:31,767
He promised me he'll lie low
at work...

59
00:03:31,900 --> 00:03:33,867
and focus on Jasmine and me.

60
00:03:37,600 --> 00:03:39,400
I hope so.

61
00:03:39,533 --> 00:03:40,500
Mom?

62
00:03:41,900 --> 00:03:42,867
Why?

63
00:03:45,200 --> 00:03:46,900
It seems that you want
to say something.

64
00:03:50,933 --> 00:03:51,900
Marj.

65
00:03:53,200 --> 00:03:54,867
Do you remember...

66
00:03:58,800 --> 00:04:01,400
Didn't Paolo promise us...

67
00:04:01,633 --> 00:04:05,033
he'd protect Jobert
at the mansion?

68
00:04:05,267 --> 00:04:09,733
But he was the one who broke
that promise...

69
00:04:09,867 --> 00:04:12,800
when he let Jobert leave.

70
00:04:15,200 --> 00:04:16,933
Marj,

71
00:04:17,067 --> 00:04:20,467
he needs to keep his promise
this time with Jasmine.

72
00:04:21,500 --> 00:04:23,100
I don't want my granddaughter
getting hurt...

73
00:04:23,233 --> 00:04:26,433
the way you and Jobert did.

74
00:04:26,567 --> 00:04:29,133
Mom, I believe in Paolo.

75
00:04:30,367 --> 00:04:32,267
I can see that...

76
00:04:32,400 --> 00:04:33,767
he's trying to make up
for everything.

77
00:04:34,800 --> 00:04:36,467
I know he can do this.

78
00:04:37,667 --> 00:04:39,333
We can handle this, Mom.

79
00:04:44,533 --> 00:04:45,500
<i> Dad...</i>

80
00:04:47,300 --> 00:04:49,400
Marj and I have something
we want to say.

81
00:04:49,533 --> 00:04:50,633
I'll go first.

82
00:04:54,133 --> 00:04:55,900
I asked for this dinner...

83
00:04:56,133 --> 00:04:57,933
because I have an announcement.

84
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:05,300
I'm stepping down as CEO
of Torrecampo Realty.

85
00:05:06,733 --> 00:05:09,133
Greg, you didn't mention
anything about this.

86
00:05:09,367 --> 00:05:12,333
Shouldn't we all be here?
Shouldn't Edward be here?

87
00:05:13,867 --> 00:05:17,867
Edward doesn't need to be here,
because, Paolo,

88
00:05:18,000 --> 00:05:20,900
I'm appointing you
as the new CEO.

89
00:05:21,033 --> 00:05:23,567
You'll be the new head
of Torrecampo Realty.

90
00:05:28,833 --> 00:05:30,100
<i> And I expect...</i>

91
00:05:30,233 --> 00:05:31,867
<i> full commitment,</i>

92
00:05:32,000 --> 00:05:33,133
<i> effective immediately.</i>

93
00:05:33,267 --> 00:05:35,100
No distractions.

94
00:05:35,267 --> 00:05:36,800
No excuses.

95
00:05:43,267 --> 00:05:44,767
Dad,

96
00:05:44,900 --> 00:05:47,133
this feels kind of sudden.

97
00:05:47,267 --> 00:05:51,100
Paolo, this transition has been
in motion for months.

98
00:05:51,233 --> 00:05:53,600
The board is ready.

99
00:05:53,733 --> 00:05:55,767
The expansion plan is ready.

100
00:05:55,900 --> 00:05:57,067
It's time.

101
00:05:57,200 --> 00:05:58,167
I know,

102
00:05:58,300 --> 00:06:01,133
but can we maybe delay it?

103
00:06:01,267 --> 00:06:02,967
I really want to focus on
my family first,

104
00:06:03,100 --> 00:06:04,900
on Marj and Jasmine.

105
00:06:06,700 --> 00:06:09,867
There's already so much
going on because of the baby.

106
00:06:10,933 --> 00:06:12,933
Dad, I don't want
to neglect them.

107
00:06:13,067 --> 00:06:14,467
They need me.

108
00:06:17,233 --> 00:06:21,567
And you think stepping back from
being CEO will help your family?

109
00:06:21,700 --> 00:06:24,200
I already agreed to let Marj
lie low...

110
00:06:24,333 --> 00:06:25,467
at work...

111
00:06:25,600 --> 00:06:28,800
so she can focus on Jasmine,
didn't I?

112
00:06:28,933 --> 00:06:31,633
We're providing for my
granddaughter's medical needs.

113
00:06:33,267 --> 00:06:36,267
<i> What Jasmine needs more...</i>

114
00:06:36,400 --> 00:06:38,500
<i> is a father...</i>

115
00:06:38,633 --> 00:06:39,967
<i> who's capable.</i>

116
00:06:40,100 --> 00:06:42,167
Who has resources and direction.

117
00:06:42,333 --> 00:06:45,567
Not a father who just sits
beside her all day.

118
00:06:47,167 --> 00:06:50,333
Paolo, you've been preparing
for this for years.

119
00:06:50,467 --> 00:06:52,500
The training, the shadowing,

120
00:06:52,633 --> 00:06:56,367
every project I've given you
this was all for this moment.

121
00:06:56,500 --> 00:06:58,233
- But maybe...
- Paolo,

122
00:06:59,400 --> 00:07:01,467
this is not up for discussion.

123
00:07:02,500 --> 00:07:04,300
You're stepping in...

124
00:07:04,433 --> 00:07:06,467
as CEO immediately.

125
00:07:20,233 --> 00:07:24,867
I thought we agreed you'd
lie low at work?

126
00:07:27,200 --> 00:07:29,433
Love, I was caught off guard,
too.

127
00:07:31,833 --> 00:07:33,867
Dad didn't give me any warning.

128
00:07:35,033 --> 00:07:36,433
I didn't expect it.

129
00:07:37,733 --> 00:07:39,433
So you accepted the position?

130
00:07:43,367 --> 00:07:46,867
I'm not saying I wanted it,
but what choice did I have?

131
00:07:48,467 --> 00:07:50,433
I've worked for this for years.

132
00:07:50,567 --> 00:07:55,300
Dad wouldn't just hand it
to Edward or to anyone else.

133
00:07:55,433 --> 00:07:57,267
He gave it to me, Love.

134
00:08:00,500 --> 00:08:03,600
Even after you said you'd help
Jasmine and me.

135
00:08:05,400 --> 00:08:08,433
Well, who are we compared
to a CEO position

136
00:08:08,567 --> 00:08:11,000
you've worked toward
your whole life?

137
00:08:19,500 --> 00:08:23,067
Love, just please trust me.

138
00:08:24,933 --> 00:08:26,133
Okay?

139
00:08:26,267 --> 00:08:27,867
I'll balance everything.

140
00:08:29,200 --> 00:08:30,267
Family.

141
00:08:31,567 --> 00:08:32,533
Work.

142
00:08:37,600 --> 00:08:38,667
For you.

143
00:08:40,633 --> 00:08:41,833
For us.

144
00:08:43,633 --> 00:08:45,833
Paolo, this isn't simple.

145
00:08:47,233 --> 00:08:50,967
Yes, Jasmine is improving,
but that doesn't mean...

146
00:08:51,100 --> 00:08:53,200
we can just relax.

147
00:08:53,333 --> 00:08:55,433
We still have to watch
her closely.

148
00:08:55,600 --> 00:08:58,767
Every feeding, every meal,
every medication.

149
00:08:58,900 --> 00:09:00,800
We can't afford to let
our guard down.

150
00:09:02,433 --> 00:09:05,267
Promise, just trust me.

151
00:09:05,400 --> 00:09:09,133
Don't think I'll leave you
behind.

152
00:09:09,267 --> 00:09:12,667
No matter how busy I get,

153
00:09:12,800 --> 00:09:14,433
I'll make time.

154
00:09:14,567 --> 00:09:15,533
Okay?

155
00:09:16,567 --> 00:09:18,500
I'm not going anywhere.

156
00:09:19,933 --> 00:09:22,567
I won't disappear on you.

157
00:09:26,533 --> 00:09:28,567
I'm trying to understand.

158
00:09:30,033 --> 00:09:32,200
I know you deserve
that position,

159
00:09:32,333 --> 00:09:34,933
and the company needs you.

160
00:09:35,067 --> 00:09:36,133
But please...

161
00:09:37,167 --> 00:09:39,567
Jasmine and I need you, too.

162
00:09:39,700 --> 00:09:41,467
Don't forget that.

163
00:09:43,200 --> 00:09:44,700
Just trust me, okay?

164
00:09:46,367 --> 00:09:47,433
Because, Love...

165
00:09:48,900 --> 00:09:50,933
I can't do this...

166
00:09:51,967 --> 00:09:53,000
without you.

167
00:10:13,600 --> 00:10:16,100
Wow, Sir Paolo's a big shot now.

168
00:10:16,233 --> 00:10:18,500
He should give me a raise.

169
00:10:18,633 --> 00:10:20,567
He's the CEO!

170
00:10:20,700 --> 00:10:23,267
Ma'am Marj is so lucky to have
Sir Pao, right?

171
00:10:23,400 --> 00:10:27,733
I'm sure their marriage is just
going to get stronger.

172
00:10:27,867 --> 00:10:29,933
I mean, they're so blessed.

173
00:10:30,067 --> 00:10:31,567
You know, honestly,

174
00:10:31,700 --> 00:10:33,600
I'm actually worried.

175
00:10:33,733 --> 00:10:35,867
What? Why?

176
00:10:36,133 --> 00:10:40,033
I've been watching Sir Greg
and Ma'am Regina's marriage...

177
00:10:40,167 --> 00:10:42,433
for years.

178
00:10:42,567 --> 00:10:46,300
Back when he wasn't that
powerful yet,

179
00:10:46,433 --> 00:10:49,333
they were so close.

180
00:10:49,467 --> 00:10:52,200
But the more he rose up,

181
00:10:52,333 --> 00:10:53,567
the more distant he became...

182
00:10:53,700 --> 00:10:56,833
and their marriage slowly
fell apart.

183
00:10:56,967 --> 00:10:59,833
Now it's Sir Paolo who's rising.

184
00:10:59,967 --> 00:11:02,000
What if what happened to them
happens to Ma'am Marj

185
00:11:02,133 --> 00:11:04,233
and Sir Paolo?

186
00:11:16,633 --> 00:11:18,133
Hey, Edward!

187
00:11:18,267 --> 00:11:19,467
Thea!

188
00:11:19,600 --> 00:11:22,300
Looks like you're excited
for Paolo.

189
00:11:22,433 --> 00:11:24,133
This is a big promotion.

190
00:11:24,267 --> 00:11:27,700
Of course, we're happy
for Paolo.

191
00:11:27,833 --> 00:11:31,367
But Edward's building
something big, too.

192
00:11:31,500 --> 00:11:35,200
He's about to launch
his business expansion.

193
00:11:35,333 --> 00:11:36,400
In Cebu.

194
00:11:39,200 --> 00:11:40,167
What are you doing?

195
00:11:41,433 --> 00:11:44,033
Why are we squeezing ourselves
in here?

196
00:11:45,200 --> 00:11:46,567
This assembly is for Paolo.

197
00:11:46,700 --> 00:11:48,500
I don't want to be part of it.

198
00:11:48,633 --> 00:11:49,500
You're the one who insisted
we come.

199
00:11:49,633 --> 00:11:52,133
We could've finished
packing earlier.

200
00:11:54,067 --> 00:11:55,667
Edward,

201
00:11:55,800 --> 00:11:57,633
we have to show up.

202
00:11:57,767 --> 00:11:59,867
Your mom invited us.

203
00:12:00,933 --> 00:12:03,333
Do you want Paolo to be
the only one shining...

204
00:12:03,467 --> 00:12:05,700
while we're invisible?

205
00:12:06,867 --> 00:12:09,500
Especially since
we're leaving Manila.

206
00:12:10,833 --> 00:12:13,033
It's better if people
see you...

207
00:12:13,167 --> 00:12:15,300
have direction even while
you're away.

208
00:12:16,367 --> 00:12:18,167
That you're doing something.

209
00:12:19,767 --> 00:12:21,700
This is optics, Edward.

210
00:12:22,733 --> 00:12:24,300
Optics.

211
00:12:24,433 --> 00:12:26,200
We show face.

212
00:12:26,333 --> 00:12:27,800
We show strength.

213
00:12:37,300 --> 00:12:38,400
Good morning, everyone.

214
00:12:38,533 --> 00:12:39,733
Good morning, Sir.

215
00:12:52,500 --> 00:12:55,267
Thank you for assembling
on such short notice.

216
00:13:06,433 --> 00:13:09,767
It is with great pride
that I announce...

217
00:13:10,900 --> 00:13:13,367
<i> the appointment of my son,</i>

218
00:13:13,500 --> 00:13:15,167
<i> Paolo Torrecampo,</i>

219
00:13:15,300 --> 00:13:19,500
as the new Chief Executive
Officer of Torrecampo Realty.

220
00:13:33,967 --> 00:13:36,600
That should've been you, Edward.

221
00:13:38,400 --> 00:13:42,200
So make sure you don't waste
your chance in Cebu.

222
00:13:46,267 --> 00:13:48,433
<i> Paolo,</i>

223
00:13:48,567 --> 00:13:50,900
<i> as you step into this role,</i>

224
00:13:51,033 --> 00:13:54,467
I expect strong leadership,

225
00:13:54,600 --> 00:13:56,233
strategic clarity,

226
00:13:56,400 --> 00:13:58,433
and full commitment.

227
00:13:58,567 --> 00:14:01,600
<i>We are entering a pivotal year,</i>

228
00:14:01,733 --> 00:14:03,967
and I trust you to bring
this company...

229
00:14:04,100 --> 00:14:06,567
to its most successful era yet.

230
00:14:07,667 --> 00:14:08,733
Cheers!

231
00:14:36,900 --> 00:14:38,667
Excuse me, excuse me.

232
00:14:46,133 --> 00:14:47,733
Hi, Marjorie.

233
00:14:51,467 --> 00:14:53,100
You know what?

234
00:14:53,233 --> 00:14:55,900
I hope you're as...

235
00:14:56,033 --> 00:14:59,000
strong and as understanding
as I am.

236
00:15:02,567 --> 00:15:04,967
Why do you say that, Mom?

237
00:15:05,100 --> 00:15:06,467
Well...

238
00:15:06,600 --> 00:15:08,467
it's kind of an open secret
that...

239
00:15:08,600 --> 00:15:13,233
Greg had other women before.

240
00:15:13,367 --> 00:15:14,933
But honestly?

241
00:15:15,067 --> 00:15:19,367
That wasn't his greatest
mistress.

242
00:15:20,400 --> 00:15:22,700
The real mistress
in my marriage...

243
00:15:22,833 --> 00:15:25,133
was the company.

244
00:15:25,267 --> 00:15:26,433
The empire.

245
00:15:26,567 --> 00:15:28,300
The responsibility.

246
00:15:28,433 --> 00:15:29,633
The position.

247
00:15:31,533 --> 00:15:33,933
Now we're the same, Marjorie.

248
00:15:35,533 --> 00:15:38,567
So you need to start
accepting now...

249
00:15:39,600 --> 00:15:42,233
that you have to share
your husband.

250
00:16:00,967 --> 00:16:02,067
Okay, okay.

251
00:16:02,200 --> 00:16:03,767
Oh, she's crying again.

252
00:16:03,900 --> 00:16:05,567
Hon, Hon.

253
00:16:05,700 --> 00:16:06,967
Make sure we didn't forget
anything...

254
00:16:07,100 --> 00:16:08,967
before we head to the airport.

255
00:16:09,133 --> 00:16:11,533
We're good, Hon, we're all set.

256
00:16:15,867 --> 00:16:17,633
Don't cry.

257
00:16:17,767 --> 00:16:19,100
Mommy's here.

258
00:16:19,233 --> 00:16:20,933
She really doesn't like me.

259
00:16:23,300 --> 00:16:24,200
Give her to me.

260
00:16:25,600 --> 00:16:27,533
Don't cry, see?

261
00:16:27,667 --> 00:16:29,933
Hello.

262
00:16:30,067 --> 00:16:31,900
Hon, I'll go get the car.

263
00:16:32,033 --> 00:16:33,367
Wait here, okay?

264
00:16:33,500 --> 00:16:35,067
Okay, we'll follow.

265
00:16:44,033 --> 00:16:46,233
We're just going far away
for a while, Sweetheart.

266
00:16:47,333 --> 00:16:49,167
So we can get stronger.

267
00:16:49,300 --> 00:16:50,600
So we can heal.

268
00:16:51,900 --> 00:16:54,400
So we can prove...

269
00:16:54,533 --> 00:16:56,200
that we deserve more.

270
00:16:57,933 --> 00:16:59,733
That we're worthy.

271
00:17:02,500 --> 00:17:05,367
And one day...

272
00:17:05,500 --> 00:17:08,167
we'll take everything
that's meant for us.

273
00:17:10,600 --> 00:17:11,833
Because you...

274
00:17:12,833 --> 00:17:15,867
you are the true heir...

275
00:17:16,033 --> 00:17:20,300
to everything
the Torrecampos have.

276
00:17:39,067 --> 00:17:41,367
<i> Good evening, Sir.</i>

277
00:17:41,600 --> 00:17:42,667
Hi, Love.

278
00:17:44,567 --> 00:17:46,100
Have you eaten?

279
00:17:50,767 --> 00:17:53,067
What about you? did you eat?

280
00:17:53,200 --> 00:17:55,433
You know, the doctor said
at the clinic earlier...

281
00:17:55,567 --> 00:17:58,633
that Jasmine gained
a little weight.

282
00:17:58,767 --> 00:18:01,033
But I'm still paranoid, Love.

283
00:18:01,167 --> 00:18:03,600
I can't shake this fear that...

284
00:18:03,733 --> 00:18:05,867
something might happen again.

285
00:18:06,000 --> 00:18:07,933
It's normal to be scared, Love.

286
00:18:08,067 --> 00:18:10,733
Especially after everything
we've been through.

287
00:18:11,767 --> 00:18:15,067
But you don't have to be strong
all by yourself.

288
00:18:20,333 --> 00:18:22,400
I'll be your strength.

289
00:18:22,567 --> 00:18:24,667
When you feel like you're about
to fall apart,

290
00:18:24,800 --> 00:18:26,600
I'll hold you up.

291
00:18:26,733 --> 00:18:28,967
When you're exhausted,

292
00:18:29,100 --> 00:18:30,533
I'll carry you.

293
00:18:33,333 --> 00:18:37,933
My husband's trying to be
a multitasker now.

294
00:18:38,067 --> 00:18:39,700
I made you a promise, didn't I?

295
00:18:40,867 --> 00:18:43,300
Just trust me.

296
00:18:43,433 --> 00:18:46,467
CEO of Torrecampo Realty,

297
00:18:46,600 --> 00:18:48,500
and CEO of my life.

298
00:18:51,033 --> 00:18:52,533
Step by step,

299
00:18:52,667 --> 00:18:55,900
we'll help Jasmine get stronger.

300
00:18:56,067 --> 00:18:58,600
It won't be easy right now,

301
00:18:58,733 --> 00:19:00,833
but one day...

302
00:19:00,967 --> 00:19:03,667
this will all feel lighter.

303
00:19:03,800 --> 00:19:06,233
We'll get there, okay?

304
00:19:06,367 --> 00:19:07,333
Us.

305
00:19:08,433 --> 00:19:09,967
Whole.

306
00:19:10,100 --> 00:19:11,233
Together.

307
00:19:46,000 --> 00:19:47,700
<i> Yes, Mom, okay.</i>

308
00:19:47,833 --> 00:19:49,967
I'll try to stop by later.

309
00:19:50,100 --> 00:19:52,100
Jasmine and I have a checkup
right now,

310
00:19:52,233 --> 00:19:53,633
and we're running a little late.

311
00:19:54,667 --> 00:19:55,833
Okay, Mom.

312
00:19:55,967 --> 00:19:57,800
I'll call you again later.

313
00:19:57,933 --> 00:19:59,267
Okay.

314
00:19:59,400 --> 00:20:00,700
- Weng?
- Yes, Ma'am?

315
00:20:00,833 --> 00:20:02,333
Can you help me with this?

316
00:20:02,500 --> 00:20:04,467
Please put...

317
00:20:04,600 --> 00:20:06,900
these client files
in the study room.

318
00:20:07,033 --> 00:20:08,600
- Yes, Ma'am.
- Thanks.

319
00:20:10,700 --> 00:20:12,967
Yolly, is Jasmine dressed
already?

320
00:20:13,100 --> 00:20:14,700
We're kind of late
for her checkup.

321
00:20:14,833 --> 00:20:15,867
Not yet, Ma'am.

322
00:20:16,000 --> 00:20:17,200
I was just about to check
on her again...

323
00:20:17,333 --> 00:20:19,667
because earlier she wasn't
answering.

324
00:20:19,800 --> 00:20:20,633
What?

325
00:20:22,267 --> 00:20:23,433
Jasmine?

326
00:20:24,733 --> 00:20:25,667
Sweetie?

327
00:20:29,000 --> 00:20:30,800
Why is her door locked?

328
00:20:31,833 --> 00:20:33,300
Sweetie?

329
00:20:33,433 --> 00:20:34,467
Jasmine?

330
00:20:35,667 --> 00:20:36,867
Jasmine!

331
00:20:38,133 --> 00:20:39,300
- Weng!
- Ma'am!

332
00:20:39,433 --> 00:20:40,367
Get the key!

333
00:20:40,500 --> 00:20:42,500
Yes, Ma'am! wait, hold on!

334
00:20:42,633 --> 00:20:43,867
Jasmine!

335
00:20:44,000 --> 00:20:46,167
Sweetie!

336
00:20:46,300 --> 00:20:48,000
Sweetie!

337
00:20:48,133 --> 00:20:49,200
Why is the door locked?

338
00:20:49,333 --> 00:20:50,733
Has it been like this
for a while?

339
00:20:50,867 --> 00:20:51,733
Jasmine!

340
00:20:51,867 --> 00:20:52,933
- Hurry!
- I'm coming!

341
00:20:53,067 --> 00:20:54,733
I have the key, Ma'am,
just a second!

342
00:20:54,867 --> 00:20:55,867
Quick!

343
00:20:56,000 --> 00:20:58,267
Here, I've got it!

344
00:20:58,400 --> 00:20:59,467
Jasmine?

345
00:21:01,233 --> 00:21:02,233
Jasmine?

346
00:21:03,267 --> 00:21:04,900
Jasmine?

347
00:21:05,033 --> 00:21:06,000
Sweetie?

348
00:21:07,033 --> 00:21:08,467
Mom?

349
00:21:08,633 --> 00:21:09,700
Jasmine!

350
00:21:10,867 --> 00:21:12,067
Sorry.

351
00:21:12,467 --> 00:21:13,267
I'll follow.

352
00:21:13,400 --> 00:21:14,767
Just a second.

353
00:21:14,900 --> 00:21:18,433
Baby, didn't I keep reminding
you not to lock the door?

354
00:21:18,567 --> 00:21:21,300
What if something happened?
what if there was an emergency?

355
00:21:21,433 --> 00:21:23,067
Please don't do that.

356
00:21:23,200 --> 00:21:24,933
Sorry, Mom.

357
00:21:25,067 --> 00:21:28,333
Maybe I didn't realize
I locked it.

358
00:21:28,467 --> 00:21:30,167
Okay, okay, just hurry up,
all right?

359
00:21:30,300 --> 00:21:31,833
We're going to be late.

360
00:21:31,967 --> 00:21:33,267
- Okay?
- Okay.

361
00:21:50,467 --> 00:21:51,633
<i> Baby!</i>

362
00:21:53,700 --> 00:21:55,167
<i> Come on, let's go!</i>

363
00:21:55,300 --> 00:21:56,567
Coming!

364
00:22:10,400 --> 00:22:12,400
Sir, everything's set up.

365
00:22:12,533 --> 00:22:14,000
It's all complete,
just like you said.

366
00:22:14,133 --> 00:22:15,767
Good, is Marj here yet?

367
00:22:16,033 --> 00:22:17,900
They're on their way home
from the clinic.

368
00:22:18,033 --> 00:22:19,133
Okay, thanks.

369
00:22:19,267 --> 00:22:21,267
Perfect timing, Sir.

370
00:22:21,400 --> 00:22:24,033
Yeah, thanks for weaving in
and out of traffic earlier.

371
00:22:24,167 --> 00:22:26,833
Oh, Sir, before you forget.

372
00:22:26,967 --> 00:22:28,600
Thank you.

373
00:22:28,733 --> 00:22:30,300
I hope Marj likes it.

374
00:22:30,433 --> 00:22:31,800
She will, Sir.

375
00:22:31,933 --> 00:22:33,033
All right, thanks.

376
00:22:33,167 --> 00:22:34,433
Just bring the stuff inside,
okay?

377
00:22:34,567 --> 00:22:35,967
- Yes, Sir.
- Okay, thank you.

378
00:22:43,600 --> 00:22:45,133
Nanny, that's okay, thank you.

379
00:22:46,600 --> 00:22:47,633
Okay.

380
00:22:54,200 --> 00:22:55,367
Love!

381
00:22:55,500 --> 00:22:56,467
Love!

382
00:22:57,500 --> 00:22:59,433
I thought I was late,
turns out...

383
00:23:00,267 --> 00:23:01,267
Here, let me help you.

384
00:23:01,400 --> 00:23:04,633
Love, the doctor said Jasmine's
results are normal.

385
00:23:04,767 --> 00:23:07,200
He gave her a new prescription
for supplements,

386
00:23:07,333 --> 00:23:09,500
so I stopped by the drugstore.

387
00:23:09,633 --> 00:23:12,633
I'm so tired, Love,
I'm exhausted.

388
00:23:18,767 --> 00:23:21,333
Oh yeah, it's our anniversary.

389
00:23:21,500 --> 00:23:23,300
You thought I forgot,
didn't you?

390
00:23:23,433 --> 00:23:24,567
Happy Anniversary.

391
00:23:28,000 --> 00:23:29,967
Happy Anniversary, Love.

392
00:23:41,500 --> 00:23:42,633
- You must be hungry, right?
- Ma'am!

393
00:23:42,767 --> 00:23:43,833
- Sir!
- Come on, let's eat.

394
00:23:43,967 --> 00:23:46,700
Ma'am, I'm so sorry.

395
00:23:46,833 --> 00:23:50,767
I can't find Jasmine's
nebulizer, she needs it.

396
00:23:50,900 --> 00:23:54,100
What? Weng, it's upstairs.

397
00:23:54,233 --> 00:23:55,333
Hold on.

398
00:23:55,500 --> 00:23:58,300
Love, you haven't opened
my gift yet.

399
00:23:58,433 --> 00:24:00,867
Love, this is important,
I'll be right back.

400
00:24:01,000 --> 00:24:04,800
Weng, why couldn't you find it?

401
00:24:23,700 --> 00:24:25,433
Love?

402
00:24:25,567 --> 00:24:28,833
Love, I'm sorry, Jasmine had
trouble breathing.

403
00:24:30,600 --> 00:24:33,167
I'll just eat quickly.

404
00:24:33,300 --> 00:24:34,667
I need to get back to her
right away.

405
00:24:34,800 --> 00:24:36,333
She might need something.

406
00:24:36,467 --> 00:24:38,333
And I also have to call mom.

407
00:24:38,467 --> 00:24:41,000
Apparently, something triggered
Jobert earlier.

408
00:24:42,400 --> 00:24:46,000
Love, maybe Yolly can watch
Jasmine for now?

409
00:24:46,133 --> 00:24:49,233
And maybe you can call your mom
tomorrow instead?

410
00:24:49,367 --> 00:24:51,500
I'm sure she can handle Jobert
on her own.

411
00:24:53,067 --> 00:24:53,867
Love,

412
00:24:55,733 --> 00:24:57,433
can you just stay? please?

413
00:25:00,167 --> 00:25:02,000
I canceled a client meeting...

414
00:25:02,167 --> 00:25:03,167
for this night.

415
00:25:06,867 --> 00:25:08,267
Let's go on another date.

416
00:25:09,967 --> 00:25:12,367
How about...

417
00:25:12,500 --> 00:25:14,467
the day after tomorrow?

418
00:25:17,067 --> 00:25:19,567
I really can't postpone
any more meetings.

419
00:25:20,767 --> 00:25:23,233
My schedule's packed this week.

420
00:25:23,367 --> 00:25:25,667
And I have a business brunch...

421
00:25:25,800 --> 00:25:27,333
this weekend.

422
00:25:27,467 --> 00:25:29,267
So maybe we can just...

423
00:25:29,400 --> 00:25:31,033
Love,

424
00:25:31,167 --> 00:25:33,700
we'll find time again.

425
00:25:33,833 --> 00:25:34,800
I promise.

426
00:25:37,033 --> 00:25:40,767
You can find time for your mom,

427
00:25:40,900 --> 00:25:42,467
for Jobert,

428
00:25:42,600 --> 00:25:43,533
for Jas.

429
00:25:44,567 --> 00:25:47,067
I just hope you can find time
for...

430
00:25:57,067 --> 00:25:58,600
Are you excited
for your birthday?

431
00:25:58,733 --> 00:26:00,500
Mom's super excited.

432
00:26:00,633 --> 00:26:02,467
She planned everything.

433
00:26:02,600 --> 00:26:04,100
And everything I want
is not allowed.

434
00:26:04,233 --> 00:26:06,267
I mean, I feel okay already.

435
00:26:06,400 --> 00:26:07,700
But she's still so strict.

436
00:26:07,833 --> 00:26:09,467
You're overreacting, Oscar.

437
00:26:09,633 --> 00:26:12,100
Jasmine, I really can't let you
do what you want.

438
00:26:13,433 --> 00:26:15,100
Ma'am Jasmine, are you...

439
00:26:15,233 --> 00:26:16,167
Ma'am Marj!

440
00:26:17,467 --> 00:26:18,400
Ouch!

441
00:26:19,867 --> 00:26:21,667
- Hey, Jasmine!
- I'll be back!

442
00:26:21,800 --> 00:26:23,000
I'm so exhausted, Mom.

443
00:26:23,133 --> 00:26:26,267
Paolo and I are still not okay.

444
00:26:26,400 --> 00:26:29,400
And my daughter feels so distant
from me now.

445
00:26:29,533 --> 00:26:31,333
She's not a baby anymore, Marj.

446
00:26:31,467 --> 00:26:33,533
If you keep scolding her
and watching her every move,

447
00:26:33,667 --> 00:26:35,100
she'll just rebel more.

448
00:26:35,233 --> 00:26:36,800
Don't focus on her too much.

449
00:26:36,933 --> 00:26:38,867
You might end up neglecting
something else.

450
00:26:39,000 --> 00:26:42,100
Maybe what you need is...

451
00:26:42,267 --> 00:26:43,467
a breather.

452
00:26:43,600 --> 00:26:45,667
Who? You?
